a.What is dialog?
Ans. A dialog is a small window on the UI of application that prompts to the 
user to make a decision or enter additional information.Dialogs does not fill 
the screen and It is normally used for modal events that requires user to take 
an action before they can further proceed.

b.How to create custom dialog?
Ans. To create custom dialog we need to create a class that extends the 
DialogFragment class and create an AlertDialog object in onCreateDialog method.

c.How to use existing dialogs
Ans.To use the existing dialog we need to create the instance of the existing 
dialog class in our activity and invoke the show method so the dialog can appear.